* Editor's note: This live event has ended. You may watch a recording above. JOHANNESBURG - Basic Education Minister Angie Motshekga is set to address the country on the department's readiness to reopen schools. Schools have been closed for over two months in a bid to slow the spread of the coronavirus. READ: COVID-19: Education unions unhappy with department Motshekga was meant to present her plan last week but rescheduled. The different provinces reported that they were at various stages of readiness and requested more time for the delivery of personal protection equipment. - Coronavirus Hotline Number: 0800 029 999 from 8am to 4pm, Monday to Friday. Help protect your loved ones by sharing this official South African government COVID-19 service with your family, friends and community. Send HI to 0600 123 456 on WhatsApp. The NICD has another Clinician Hotline to improve #COVID19 communication and support for healthcare providers. The Clinician Hotline is 0800 11 1131, operating 24 hrs. The Public Hotline is 0800 029 999 also operating 24hrs.